          Neuer is the best gk in the world, Bayern really suffered without him. But day by day and especially game by game Ulreich is coming to his own. He is looking a very decent gk perhaps the best back up keeper in the world. Although the scoreline is not great for Bayern. But at the end of the day, I'm satisfied. Jup Heynkes is tactically is very flexible unlike Peter Bosz of Bvb or Carlo Ancellotti. 53 percent of possession that too considering Bayern Munich are joint second with psg on Possession stats on domestic league. That shows the flexibility of Jup Heynkes. Yeah, FOCUSED possession does win you lot of games. But sometimes you have to forego this obsession to win games. You have to tactically flexible. Bayern munich can play possession football if they put Rudy, Alcantra and Kimmich as midfielders. They can play gegenpressing if they use guys like Martinez, Tollisso and Vidal. A Clever coach which I hope Heynkes is could use these two types of tactics and players at his disposal.
